Project Motivation & Purpose
I developed this project to demonstrate how Generative AI and workflow automation can democratize institutional-grade financial analysis. My goal was to build an autonomous agent capable of synthesizing raw market data into actionable investment theses, effectively simulating the workflow of a Junior Equity Analyst.

This tool solves the problem of "analysis paralysis" by instantly aggregating real-time financials and news sentiment, transforming complex datasets into a clear, readable investment verdict.

Functional Overview
This application functions as an end-to-end "AI Hedge Fund" dashboard. It orchestrates a pipeline that moves from raw data ingestion to high-level reasoning.

The Workflow:

Frontend Interface: A responsive React and Tailwind CSS dashboard accepts a stock ticker (e.g., AAPL, NVDA).

Orchestration (n8n): The request triggers a complex automation workflow in n8n:

Market Data: Fetches real-time price, P/E ratios, PEG, ROE, and Debt/Equity metrics via the Finnhub API.

Sentiment Data: Aggregates the top 5 relevant news headlines from major financial outlets (Bloomberg, WSJ, Reuters) via NewsAPI.

AI Analysis: The aggregated data is fed into Llama 3.3 70B (via Groq). The LLM is prompt-engineered to act as a Senior Analyst, performing:

Fundamental Analysis: Evaluating financial health based on the fetched metrics.

Qualitative Analysis: Assessing risks based on news sentiment.

Valuation Verdict: Determining if the stock is undervalued, overvalued, or fairly valued.

Visualization: The resulting report is rendered back to the user in a clean, Markdown-formatted financial report.

Tech Stack
Frontend: React, Tailwind CSS, DOMPurify

Backend/Orchestration: n8n (Workflow Automation)

AI/LLM: Llama 3.3 70B (via Groq API)

Financial APIs: Finnhub (Market Data), NewsAPI (Sentiment)

